# Column accuracy for a SHALLOW interpolation — the expr starts at a column ≤ 8,
# where the probe's compensated //line (exprCol − len("_gsxuse(")) would be < 1,
# an invalid //line column. The skeleton instead breaks the probe across lines
# and anchors the expr's own //line at its source column, so the diagnostic (and
# go-to-definition, and the dev-overlay caret) land exactly on the identifier.
#
# Here the body is indented with TWO SPACES, so `bad` sits at column 4:
# "  {bad}" = space(1) space(2) {(3) b(4). Before this fix the fallback reported
# it at column 11 (4 + len("_gsxuse(") − 1), drifting the caret past the value.
-- input.gsx --
package views

var _ = 0

component Page() {
  {bad}
}
-- diagnostics.golden --
6:4: undefined: bad
